## 6. C++ Implementation (with line-by-line meaning)

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

// Tree ka structure
struct Node {
    int data;          // value store karega
    Node* left;        // left child
    Node* right;       // right child

    Node(int val) {    // constructor
        data = val;
        left = right = NULL;
    }
};

// Preorder function
void preorder(Node* root) {

    // Agar node exist nahi karta
    if (root == NULL) return;

    // Step 1: current node visit karo
    cout << root->data << " ";

    // Step 2: left subtree
    preorder(root->left);

    // Step 3: right subtree
    preorder(root->right);
}

int main() {
    // Tree banate hain
    Node* root = new Node(1);   // root
    root->left = new Node(2);   // left child
    root->right = new Node(3);  // right child

    preorder(root); // function call

    return 0;
}
```

---

## Code Explanation (line by line simple 🔍)

* `struct Node` → tree ka ek node define kar raha hai

* `data` → value store karega

* `left/right` → pointers for children

* `preorder(root)`:

  * `if (root == NULL)` → base case (stop)
  * `cout << root->data` → sabse pehle current node print
  * `preorder(root->left)` → left side jao
  * `preorder(root->right)` → right side jao

---

## Final Summary 🧠

👉 Preorder = **Root → Left → Right**
👉 DFS traversal hai
👉 Mostly recursion se solve hota hai
👉 Time Complexity = **O(n)** (har node ek baar visit hota hai) ([GeeksforGeeks][1])

